</a><br>Hodges..a 64 year old retired cop gets a letter from one of the worst characters I've ever met in a book. The hunt is on. <br>I got swept up in this book and now I'm crying a little (yes my cold heart does that occasionally). This book has characters that I was cheering so hard for by the end of it that my family was looking at me like I was nuts. (OK so it's happened before-shut up)<br><br>This isn't normal King though. This is crime fiction with a hard on.<br>There is a bit of overload on the computer stuff. Enough to scare the shit out of you at least. Who cares?! <br><a href="http://imgur.com/9jwK1rn" rel="nofollow noopener">
