<div id="review_1775434646" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1775434646" />
    <a title="Annemarie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27544490-annemarie"><img alt="Annemarie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1640291254p2/27544490.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1775434646?book_show_action=true">Jan 05, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Annemarie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Annemarie" href="/user/show/27544490-annemarie">Annemarie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="paperback 9783453438460" href="/book/show/51838849-mr-mercedes">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27544490-annemarie?shelf=read-in-german">read-in-german</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1775434646" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13493167540826558387">There&apos;s something I need to mention beforehand:<br/>I was in a giant reading slump last year and read less books than ever before. I made it one of my biggest New Year&apos;s resolutions to get back on track. So I made sure to pick a book by my favourite author as my first read of the year. <br/>However, I was still nervous that I might not be able to get out of my slump, especially because I normally don&apos;t read detective stories anymore. I used to read them constantly when I was younger, but after a while I g</span>
  <span id="freeText13493167540826558387" style="display:none">There's something I need to mention beforehand:<br />I was in a giant reading slump last year and read less books than ever before. I made it one of my biggest New Year's resolutions to get back on track. So I made sure to pick a book by my favourite author as my first read of the year. <br />However, I was still nervous that I might not be able to get out of my slump, especially because I normally don't read detective stories anymore. I used to read them constantly when I was younger, but after a while I got tired of them. It seemed like they all followed the same pattern. They often had unbelievable plot twists, which came out of nowhere and were over the top. I found myself rolling my eyes and being annoyed. That's definitely NOT how I want to spend my reading time, so I stopped picking them up.<br /><br />But I mean, this is Stephen King, right? I was sure he could create a detective story I'd enjoy. And well - (unsurprisingly) I was right! FINALLY I read about a detective that didn't leave me in utter disbelief. Sure, Bill Hodges still shares some of the traits (and dare I say, "clichés") that are included in the majority of the books of this genre. But he had enough charm to make me like him. And he had enough other character traits to make him realistic. I enjoyed reading his internal monologues, how he came to his conclusions and so on. All the other characters made an impression on me as well - they all harmonized in the perfect way. <br />The suspense was on every page, no sentence was too much or unnecessary, I kept guessing what would happen next, I didn't want to stop reading - so all the things that are supposed to happen while reading a good crime book finally happened to me again! <br /><br />I went into the book almost completely blind, I only knew what would happen in the very first chapter. And I think this was the perfect way to experience the story. There were many things I didn't expect to happen, but they all made sense and didn't come out of thin air.<br />So yeah, I'm definitely glad I gave this genre another try! I couldn't have chosen a better book to start off the new year.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13493167540826558387" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


